HEADWORD: Opulent
<hw>Op"u*lent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>opulens</ets>, <ets>opulentus</ets>, fr. <ets>ops</ets>,
<ets>opis</ets>, power, wealth, riches, perh. akin to E. <ets>apt</ets>:
cf. F. <ets>opulent</ets>. Cf. <er>Copious</er>, <er>Couple</er>,
<er>Office</er>.]</ety> <def>Having a large estate or property; wealthy;
rich; affluent; <as>as, an <ex>opulent</ex> city; an <ex>opulent</ex>
citizen</as>.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Op"u*lent*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

